column5: Got over to KCs Landing for a little fishing.Havnt been there for a while.Needed a fishing fix and a walleye supper.Was busy there this morning.The Glacier had some guys staying in it a few days and more guys in one of the cabins.Actually got there early around 7:30 and glad I did.Fishing was pretty fast and got some right away on a bare hair jig.Caught maybe around 20 real fast in first hour and then it slowed down right after I had something big on,either a muskie or a pike.Caught one decent walleye but rest all eater sized.After 9 or so it was very slow and only saw the occasional fish on my sonar.Good time to go home and clean my fish.
Cleaned and ready for the frypan tonight.
I recall a similar looking plate like that awhile ago.same ending also,killer krumbs for us!
Tonight Silvia put them in parchment paper and baked them with some lemon slices.Pretty good also.Just like changing it up and not use oil or breading all the time.
Silvia knows how to get'er done,I could tell by the taste of her pie.

I'll tell Rod.We are back in business.We got the oven element we ordered yesterday and put it in.So yesterday the baking started again with zucchini bread which is a favorite of mine and tonight baked fish.Back in business.I see blueberry pies in the future.
Always nice to have a oven that works lol,Silvia puts enough blueberry's in her pie to choke a big bruin of a bear!
On our August trip to Mahkwa one of the guys surprised us with baked walleye filets. Just a bit of lemon pepper, olive oil, and a pinch of garlic. It was a great change up from fried.

Had walleye last night night in parchment paper with some spices and couple of lemon slices.Its really good that way.Nothing like all the oil and crumbs but good to change things up especially the number of fish we get to eat.Had some greens and baked sweet potatoes with the fish.
